# Typed IPC Boundaries

Per DESIGN.md: **The preload bridge and IPC handlers share a single `IpcChannels` type definition. No `any` on IPC boundaries.** **Zod at every boundary.**

## Rules

- All channel names come from a shared `ipc-channels.ts` (or equivalent) constants file.
- Every IPC handler must validate incoming args and outgoing results with Zod schemas before use or return.
- The preload script exposes only typed methods; `invoke`/`send` signatures must match `IpcChannels`.
- Do not use `any` for IPC payload types. Use inferred types from Zod or explicit interfaces.

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — typed handler with Zod validation
import { z } from 'zod'
const profileSchema = z.object({ id: z.string().uuid(), ... })

ipcMain.handle('profile:save', async (_, raw) => {
  const parsed = profileSchema.safeParse(raw)
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error('Invalid payload')
  await profileService.save(parsed.data)
})
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — untyped, no validation
ipcMain.handle('profile:save', async (_, data: any) => {
  await profileService.save(data)
})
```
